<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-10-28T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-10-28T11:00:00-05:00" n="329" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d329">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">863.51/847: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in Austria</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Washburn</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-10-28T11:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">October 28,
                                        1927—11 a.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>20. Your 54, September 20, 10 a.m. and despatch 1532, September 20. In
                            opinion of law officers of this Government, the Secretary of the
                            Treasury has no power to act further under the Joint Resolution approved
                            April 6, 1922, and a new enabling act of Congress would be necessary to
                            enable him to take the suggested action.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Olds</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>